title.narrative: STATE INSTITUTIONS - MANAGEMENT AND INTERSECTORIAL

description.narrative: State institutions have management and intersectoral coordination capacities to increase coverage and improve the quality of services that favor the survival and full development of children under 6 years of age, especially those in situations of exclusion., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence (Covid), Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, children under 6 years of age in situations of exclusion will reach full development in their family and community environments, with inclusive and equitable access to social programmes and services, even in emergency situations.

description.narrative: A total of 140,244 children have benefited from early childhood education through alternative approaches,such as home visits; This has been possible because 8,253 health workers, educators from MIFAN and Los Pipitos have developed skills in CCD, thereby enabling 48,989 mothers, fathers and caregivers of children under three years of age and 65,691 children between 4 and 6 years of age to receive training in parenting practices.With the support of UNICEF and other UN agencies, vaccination coverage against COVID-19 has reached 47%. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/01/2022
